messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, I'm seeing a plane.
Good morning. Can you describe what you're seeing?
We just saw a big airliner being escorted by two fighter planes.
Two fighter planes? Can you give me more details?
It was flying low over the Medical Center. I thought it might crash into us.
Hold on a second. Let me check. [Pause] Hello? There's nothing going on, they're just testing.
All right. Thank you. I'll let you know if something else happens.

For whatever it's worth, I'm a motorist with a cell phone. I was coming through Journal Square just now. A four-engine passenger plane was making a sharp bank, and there was a military fighter plane flying right alongside it.
A passenger plane and a military plane were flying over Journal Square?
Yes, they were high up, and the passenger plane was making a sharp turn. The military plane was right alongside it. It didn't look right, so I thought I'd let someone know.
Okay, sir. We will notify the relevant authorities. Thank you for letting us know.
The F-18 chasing a big commercial plane round and round over downtown Jersey?
Yes, we're aware of it.
Okay, thank you.
Well, there's a plane.
Yes, ma'am. Please don't worry. It's just a test.
No, no, it's impossible. There's still fighter planes.
Ma'am, the planes are just doing tests. There's nothing to worry about.
No, that was a fighter and a commercial airplane. It went to Newark, and it came back towards me. I got pictures of it.
All right, ma'am. There's nothing to worry about. It's just testing, okay?
I just had two unusual aircraft fly really close over my building. Is there something going on?
Yes, they're testing. There's nothing to be alarmed about.
Okay, thank you.
This is Wayne T. Garden from the 30 Hudson building in Jersey City.
Yes, we're aware. They're doing tests. The police are aware of it.
Hold on because my building is starting to evacuate.
No, you don't have to evacuate. They're doing testing, and the police are aware of it.
Hello, ma'am?
Yes, sir.
I can hear you. Your building is evacuating?
Yes, but you say it's a test?
Yes, it's just a test. There's nothing to worry about.
Okay, and it is a test? Who's testing?
The authorities are conducting test runs. There's nothing to worry about.
Hi, do you know why there's an airplane flying low?
Yes, ma'am. The police are well aware of it. They're doing test runs.
Okay, thanks.
I'm in number 480 Washington Boulevard building and we're seeing a big jumbo plane circling around this area.
They're testing. There's nothing to worry about.
Hello, my name is Elsa Salazar.
Ma'am, what is your emergency?
The emergency is an airplane.
Ma'am, it's a test run. The police are aware of it. There's nothing for you to worry about.
What's going on with this airplane?
It's a test run. The police are aware of it. Have a good day.
I'm at a building in Jersey City, 77 Hudson Street, and there's an airliner circling.
They're doing testing on the planes. There's nothing to worry about.
There's a whole crew here in emergency mode.
The police are aware of it, sir. We have numerous calls on it.
Hi, do you know why there are planes hovering above?
Yes, ma'am. They're doing test runs.
Hi, this is a call from Plaza 5 downtown. We have a complaint.
Yes, it's a test. There's nothing to worry about. You can see it on the news.
